All symbols show higher MDD with aggressive sizing (expected). The relative ranking across symbols is preserved.

---

## 4. Conclusions

### What the Aggressive Sizing Reveals

1. **Override advantage is stable** — Override mode maintains 28.5% lower MDD regardless of sizing aggressiveness
2. **Synthetic data limitation persists** — Groups remain identical because synthetic data's statistical structure doesn't differentiate override point contributions
3. **The ablation framework works correctly** — the per-symbol differences between Conservative and Aggressive runs prove the sizing changes propagate through the system

### Next Steps for Real Differentiation

| Priority | Experiment | Expected Outcome |
|----------|-----------|-----------------|
| **1** | Run on 100+ real symbols | Groups will show different MDD/Sharpe contributions on real data |
| **2** | Run individual point ablation (points 01, 64, 72, 48, 52, 15, 02) | Show marginal contribution of each |
| **3** | Walk-forward with ablation | Verify group stability over time |
| **4** | Test combined "Core Dynamic + Risk & Tail + Volatility" vs Full | Validate the minimal high-impact set |

